# Dependency Injection Guide

## DI Token System

This project uses a centralized DI token system to manage dependencies and avoid circular dependencies.

## Creating DI Tokens

### 1. Define Tokens in `constants.ts`
```typescript
export const {ModuleName}DiToken = {
  // Use case tokens
  CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE: Symbol('CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE'),
  UPDATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE: Symbol('UPDATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE'),
  GET_{ENTITY}_BY_ID_USE_CASE: Symbol('GET_{ENTITY}_BY_ID_USE_CASE'),
  
  // Repository tokens
  {ENTITY}_REPOSITORY: Symbol('{ENTITY}_REPOSITORY'),
  
  // Service tokens
  {ENTITY}_SERVICE: Symbol('{ENTITY}_SERVICE'),
  
  // Query service tokens
  {ENTITY}_QUERY_SERVICE: Symbol('{ENTITY}_QUERY_SERVICE'),
} as const;
```

### 2. Register Providers in Module
```typescript
@Module({
  providers: [
    // Use cases with DI tokens
    {
      provide: {ModuleName}DiToken.CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE,
      useClass: Create{Entity}UseCase,
    },
    
    // Repositories with DI tokens
    {
      provide: {ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_REPOSITORY,
      useClass: Drizzle{Entity}Repository,
    },
    
    // Services
    {
      provide: {ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_SERVICE,
      useClass: {Entity}Service,
    },
    
    // Domain mappers (no DI tokens needed)
    {Entity}Mapper,
    
    // Event handlers
    {Entity}CreatedEventHandler,
  ],
})
export class {ModuleName}Module {}
```

## Using DI Tokens

### 1. Inject in Use Cases
```typescript
@Injectable()
export class Create{Entity}UseCase extends Command<Create{Entity}Dto, {Entity}> {
  constructor(
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_REPOSITORY)
    private readonly {entity}Repository: I{Entity}Repository,
    
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_SERVICE)
    private readonly {entity}Service: I{Entity}Service,
  ) {
    super();
  }
}
```

### 2. Inject in Controllers
```typescript
@Controller('{entity}')
export class {Entity}Controller {
  constructor(
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.CREATE_{ENTITY}_USE_CASE)
    private readonly create{Entity}UseCase: ICreate{Entity}UseCase,
    
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.GET_{ENTITY}_BY_ID_USE_CASE)
    private readonly get{Entity}ByIdUseCase: IGet{Entity}ByIdUseCase,
  ) {}
}
```

### 3. Inject in Event Handlers
```typescript
@EventsHandler({Entity}CreatedEvent)
export class {Entity}CreatedEventHandler implements IEventHandler<{Entity}CreatedEvent> {
  constructor(
    @Inject({ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_SERVICE)
    private readonly {entity}Service: I{Entity}Service,
  ) {}
}
```

## Cross-Module Dependencies

### 1. Forward References for Circular Dependencies (though try to avoid it to keep modules loosed coupled)
```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [forwardRef(() => OtherModule)],
  // ... rest of module config
})
export class {ModuleName}Module {}
```

### 2. Importing Shared Services
```typescript
// Shared services are automatically available
@Injectable()
export class {Entity}Service {
  constructor(
    private readonly paginationService: PaginationService, // From shared module
    private readonly slugService: SlugService, // From shared module
  ) {}
}
```

### 3. Using Core Services
```typescript
// Core services are globally available
@Injectable()
export class {Entity}UseCase {
  constructor(
    private readonly logger: Logger, // From core module
  ) {}
}
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Token Naming Convention
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for token names
- Be descriptive: `CREATE_COMPANY_USE_CASE` not just `CREATE_USE_CASE`
- Group related tokens together

### 2. Provider Registration
- Always use DI tokens for use cases, repositories, and services
- Domain mappers don't need DI tokens (they're stateless)
- Event handlers don't need DI tokens unless they have complex dependencies

### 3. Interface Usage
- Define interfaces for all injectable services
- Use interfaces in constructor parameters
- This enables better testing and loose coupling

### 4. Module Exports
```typescript
@Module({
  // ... providers and imports
  exports: [
    // Export what other modules need
    {ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_SERVICE,
    {ModuleName}DiToken.{ENTITY}_REPOSITORY,
  ],
})
export class {ModuleName}Module {}
```

## Testing with DI Tokens

```typescript
describe('CreateCompanyUseCase', () => {
  let useCase: CreateCompanyUseCase;
  let mockRepository: jest.Mocked<ICompanyRepository>;

  beforeEach(async () => {
    const module = await Test.createTestingModule({
      providers: [
        CreateCompanyUseCase,
        {
          provide: CompanyDiToken.COMPANY_REPOSITORY,
          useValue: mockRepository,
        },
      ],
    }).compile();

    useCase = module.get<CreateCompanyUseCase>(CreateCompanyUseCase);
    mockRepository = module.get(CompanyDiToken.COMPANY_REPOSITORY);
  });
});
```
